      • toBytes

        public abstract java.nio.ByteBuffer toBytes(T object)
        Returns a new ByteBuffer b with a serialized representation of object between b.position() and b.limit(). b.order() is undefined.

      • fromBytes

        public abstract T fromBytes(java.nio.ByteBuffer b)
        Returns the object whose serialized representation is in b between b.position() and b.limit(). The value of b.order() when the method is called is undefined, and this method may modify it as well as b.position() and b.limit().

        The method may throw a RuntimeException if it determines that the sequence of bytes in b was not generated by toBytes(T). This includes corrupted data as well as trailing bytes.
